HEADWORD: Sectarianism
<hw>Sec*ta"ri*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality
or character of a sectarian; devotion to the interests of a party;
excess of partisan or denominational zeal; adherence to a separate
church organization.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

